{"id":"harim","term":"Harim","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Flat-nosed. (1.) The head of the second course of priests (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 24:8\">1 Chr. 24:8</a>). (2.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:32\">Ezra 2:32</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:39\">39</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 7:35\">Neh. 7:35</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 7:42\">42</a>. (3.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 3:11\">Neh. 3:11</a>. (4.) 12:3. (5.) 10:5</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 24:8","Ezra 2:32","Ezra 2:39","Nehemiah 7:35","Nehemiah 7:42","Nehemiah 3:11"]}